## MAEMO COMPLIANCE — DEPLOYMENT RULES

Read this entire file before making any changes.

════════════════════════════════════════
SERVER
════════════════════════════════════════

Server: 65.109.7.45 (Hetzner, billable server)
User: maemo-compliance (isolated)
App dir: /opt/maemo-compliance/app
Env file: /opt/maemo-compliance/.env
SSH: ssh -i ~/.ssh/billable_hetzner billable@65.109.7.45
     then: sudo su - maemo-compliance

════════════════════════════════════════
DOMAINS
════════════════════════════════════════

Frontend (Angular portal): https://maemo-compliance.co.za
  → nginx proxies to 127.0.0.1:3020 (maemo-compliance-portal container)

API (.NET 8): https://api.maemo-compliance.co.za
  → nginx proxies to 127.0.0.1:8090 (maemo-compliance-api container)

Email: admin@maemo-compliance.co.za (Resend, domain verified)

════════════════════════════════════════
DOCKER
════════════════════════════════════════

Deploy command:
  cd /opt/maemo-compliance/app
  docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d

Containers:
  maemo-compliance-postgres  (postgres:16-alpine, internal only)
  maemo-compliance-api       (ghcr.io/ntokyb/maemo-compliance-api:latest, :8090)
  maemo-compliance-workers   (ghcr.io/ntokyb/maemo-compliance-workers:latest)
  maemo-compliance-portal    (ghcr.io/ntokyb/maemo-compliance-portal:latest, :3020)

Network: app_default (shared with other apps on server)
  → always use container names not localhost for inter-container comms
  → maemo-compliance-postgres is the DB hostname inside containers

Images built from:
  API:     docker build -t ghcr.io/ntokyb/maemo-compliance-api:latest -f MaemoCompliance.Api/Dockerfile .
  Workers: docker build -t ghcr.io/ntokyb/maemo-compliance-workers:latest -f workers/src/MaemoCompliance.Workers/Dockerfile .
  Portal:  docker build -t ghcr.io/ntokyb/maemo-compliance-portal:latest -f frontend/Dockerfile .

Portal Dockerfile requires frontend/nginx.conf to exist.
If it does not exist the portal build WILL FAIL.
frontend/nginx.conf must always be committed.

════════════════════════════════════════
MIGRATIONS
════════════════════════════════════════

Production images have NO dotnet SDK — cannot run
dotnet ef inside running containers.

Run migrations using the SDK image with --connection flag:

  NETWORK=$(docker inspect maemo-compliance-api \
    --format '{{range $k,$v := .NetworkSettings.Networks}}{{$k}}{{end}}')

  docker run --rm \
    --network "$NETWORK" \
    -v /opt/maemo-compliance/app:/src \
    -w /src \
    mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:8.0 \
    sh -c 'dotnet restore MaemoCompliance.sln --verbosity quiet && \
      dotnet tool install --global dotnet-ef --verbosity quiet && \
      export PATH=$PATH:/root/.dotnet/tools && \
      dotnet ef database update \
        --project infrastructure/src/MaemoCompliance.Infrastructure \
        --startup-project MaemoCompliance.Api \
        --connection "Host=maemo-compliance-postgres;Port=5432;Database=maemo-compliance;Username=maemo-compliance;Password=YOUR_PASSWORD"'

Run migrations BEFORE starting the API container.
Run migrations AFTER every new migration is added.
Verify migrations: docker exec maemo-compliance-postgres psql
  -U maemo-compliance -d maemo-compliance
  -c "SELECT migration_id FROM \"__EFMigrationsHistory\" ORDER BY migration_id;"

════════════════════════════════════════
ENV FILE
════════════════════════════════════════

Location: /opt/maemo-compliance/.env (NOT in repo, gitignored)
Symlinked: /opt/maemo-compliance/app/.env → /opt/maemo-compliance/.env

Required variables (never commit real values):
  ASPNETCORE_ENVIRONMENT=Production
  ConnectionStrings__MaemoDatabase=Host=maemo-compliance-postgres;Port=5432;Database=maemo-compliance;Username=maemo-compliance;Password=...
  POSTGRES_DB=maemo-compliance
  POSTGRES_USER=maemo-compliance
  POSTGRES_PASSWORD=...
  AZURE_AUTHORITY=https://login.microsoftonline.com/{tenant-id}
  AZURE_AUDIENCE=api://{api-client-id}
  AZURE_CLIENT_ID={spa-client-id}
  Resend__ApiKey=re_...
  Resend__FromAddress=admin@maemo-compliance.co.za
  App__PublicPortalUrl=https://maemo-compliance.co.za
  Features__SelfServiceSignupEnabled=true
  Features__BillingEnabled=false
  Storage__ForceLocalFileStorage=true
  Storage__LocalBasePath=/app/files
  Admin__DemoSeedApiKey=...

CRITICAL: Passwords with ! or # in bash heredocs cause
  "event not found" errors. Always use single quotes
  or write the .env file directly with nano.

════════════════════════════════════════
GIT ON SERVER
════════════════════════════════════════

The app directory is owned by maemo-compliance user.
Root will get "dubious ownership" errors.
Always git as maemo-compliance:

  sudo -u maemo-compliance bash << 'EOF'
  git config --global user.email "admin@maemo-compliance.co.za"
  git config --global user.name "Maemo Compliance"
  git config --global --add safe.directory /opt/maemo-compliance/app
  cd /opt/maemo-compliance/app
  git pull origin main
  EOF

Deploy key: /home/maemo-compliance/.ssh/deploy_key
SSH config for git: core.sshCommand=ssh -i /home/maemo-compliance/.ssh/deploy_key

════════════════════════════════════════
CI/CD
════════════════════════════════════════

GitHub repo: github.com/ntokyb/maemo-compliance
GitHub Actions: .github/workflows/ci.yml

Jobs:
  unit        → dotnet test MaemoCompliance.UnitTests
  integration → dotnet test MaemoCompliance.IntegrationTests (Testcontainers)
  frontend    → npm ci && npm run build --configuration production
  docker-build → builds and pushes 3 images to GHCR
  deploy      → SSH to server, git pull, docker compose up -d

Required GitHub secrets:
  MAEMO_COMPLIANCE_SSH_HOST    = 65.109.7.45
  MAEMO_COMPLIANCE_SSH_USER    = maemo-compliance
  MAEMO_COMPLIANCE_SSH_KEY     = /home/maemo-compliance/.ssh/deploy_key (private)
  MAEMO_COMPLIANCE_STAGING_URL = https://maemo-compliance.co.za
  MAEMO_COMPLIANCE_API_STAGING_URL = https://api.maemo-compliance.co.za

Packages permission: write (required for GHCR push)
Set in ci.yml: permissions: contents: read, packages: write

════════════════════════════════════════
ARCHITECTURE
════════════════════════════════════════

Solution: MaemoCompliance.sln
Namespace: MaemoCompliance.*
Pattern: Clean Architecture + MediatR

Projects:
  MaemoCompliance.Api          → main API host
  MaemoCompliance.Application  → use cases, commands, queries
  MaemoCompliance.Domain       → entities, value objects
  MaemoCompliance.Infrastructure → EF Core, Resend, Azure AD, SharePoint
  MaemoCompliance.Workers      → background jobs
  MaemoCompliance.UnitTests    → xUnit + FluentAssertions
  MaemoCompliance.IntegrationTests → xUnit + WebApplicationFactory + Testcontainers

Frontend: Angular (frontend/)
  Build output: dist/maemo-compliance-portal/browser/
  Served by: nginx inside portal container
  nginx config: frontend/nginx.conf (MUST exist or build fails)
  Angular routing: all routes → index.html (SPA)

Auth: Azure AD (MSAL)
  API validates JWT from Azure AD
  SPA uses MSAL Angular library
  Test users must exist in the Azure AD tenant

Email: Resend
  From: admin@maemo-compliance.co.za
  Domain verified in Resend dashboard
  Provider: ResendEmailSender (registered when Resend__ApiKey is set)
  Fallback: LoggingEmailSender (when key is empty, dev/test only)

════════════════════════════════════════
NGINX
════════════════════════════════════════

Config: /etc/nginx/sites-available/maemo-compliance
Enabled: /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/maemo-compliance (symlink)
TLS cert: /etc/letsencrypt/live/maemo-compliance.co.za/

After any nginx config change:
  nginx -t && systemctl reload nginx

TLS renewal: automatic via certbot systemd timer
Manual renew: certbot renew --nginx

Portal serves Angular SPA — nginx config must have:
  try_files $uri $uri/ /index.html;
  (without this all Angular routes return 404)

════════════════════════════════════════
WHAT MUST NEVER BE DONE
════════════════════════════════════════

NEVER use docker restart — does not reload .env
ALWAYS use: docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d

NEVER run dotnet ef inside the API container
  (no SDK in production image)
ALWAYS use the SDK migration container pattern above

NEVER commit real secrets to the repo
NEVER commit .env files (they are gitignored)
NEVER hardcode connection strings in code

NEVER suggest AWS, GCP, or Azure hosting
ALWAYS use Hetzner (65.109.7.45)

NEVER use heredoc with passwords containing ! or #
  bash history expansion breaks them
ALWAYS use single quotes or nano for .env editing

